i always loaded up stuns open up with ur first largest nuke a second into her first cast, then stun then nuke, she dies rather fast. the pet beat on me to break the camp but never interrupted me and its quite easy to deal with<br>
<br>
if u still have troubles switch to the lower nuke that has the stun effect built in, forget the name for that one. and use it if ur stun doesnt stick <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elrond>elrond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://eonwethewizard.homestead.com/files/e.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/9/01 7:46:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eonwethewizard.homestead.com/files/pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happ</span><hr size=1> Happ casts hard, so dont let her cast. Also, put up a shieldskin, as it helps greatly. At level 45-47 this was my strategy:<br>
<br>
When she pops, cast in this order:<br>
Tishan's Clash, Root/emobilize, Thunderstrike, Conflag.<br>
<br>
That's it , she is dead. The stun stops her from making a pet and gets resisted less then root, so i open with it. Thunderstrike is great because of the interrupt stun which stops her first cast on you. You will then be able to land conflag as she is casting her last dd. If you are far enough away, you can pull off conflag even if root breaks.<br>
<br>
The skin helps when root gets resisted or if she manages to cast on you. If root breaks just use stun, step back reroot and then conflag or Thunderstrike as you see best.<br>
<br>
Very safe camp if you know to stun and interrupt. <p>              <img src="http://eonwethewizard.homestead.com/files/sig.jpg" border="0"
